<TEXT>
police on wednesday seized three 
convicts who broke jail in a bloody shootout but eight remained 
free including a man convicted of 12 murders in mexico and the 
united states a prison chief said 
gabriel nahas director of chihuahua states 14 prisons said 
authorities now have captured 26 of the 34 convicts who fled from 
the states largest penitentiary tuesday in a break that killed 
four people and wounded eight 
nahas said the prison at chihuahua city was quiet wednesday but 
that two of the most notorious inmates were still fugitives 
one is alfonso parga palafox convicted as a drug trafficker who 
murdered seven people in mexico and five in the united states the 
other is gerardo noe payan convicted of killing three chihuahua 
university students in 1987 nahas said in an interview 
he said two inmates and two guards were shot to death in the 
violence that broke out tuesday afternoon and four prisoners and 
four guards were injured 
the director said the break was led by convicted drug trafficker 
juan de dios levario quiroz who was shot to death trying to get 
away 
nahas said the prisoners surprised six guards overpowered them 
and took away their weapons 
apparently it was all planned several prisoners had guns and 
two vehicles awaited them outside leo zavala news editor of 
diario de chihuahua newspaper said tuesday 
he said authorities conducted a weapons search in the cell 
blocks wednesday and found two guns both taken from guards and 
hidden after the rioting 
visiting hours were suspended at the penitentiary which houses 
1500 inmates in the capital city of chihuahua 225 miles south of 
el paso texas zavala reported 
all the escapers are believed to still be in chihuahua state and 
a search is under way with helicopters planes cars and roadblocks 
on major highways nahas said 
mexico does not have the death penalty the maximum prison 
sentence is 40 years 
</TEXT>
