the next year the great american flag was shunted to the less 
glamorous east potomac park then the banner was dumped in a dark 
warehouse in a remote corner of washington its been there ever 
since 
here we have the flag always in the news people thinking of 
ways to legislate respect for the flag silverfine said and 
here we have the biggest american flag which because of its sheer 
size has the power to uplift the spirits and its sitting in this 
big almost empty warehouse 
