<TEXT>
hundreds of thousands of pilgrims 
wound up their rituals at islams holiest sites wednesday while the 
moslem world mourned the deaths of 1426 people in the worst 
pilgrimage tragedy in modern history 
iranian president hashemi rafsanjani said the tragedy proved the 
saudi royal family is incompetent to administer islams holiest 
shrines 
rafsanjanis harsh remarks ended hopes that relations might 
improve after the generous relief supplies saudi arabia sent to 
iranian earthquake victims 
most pilgrims were leaving the plains of mina by sunset 
wednesday and heading for mecca to make a farewell circle of the 
kaaba islams holiest shrine to which moslems turn five times in 
daily prayer 
part of the days rituals also included the stoning of the 
devil for a third time at gamarat aqabah the site where the 
pilgrims were headed when the tragic stampede occurred monday 
saudi authorities were setting up a large area at the holy sites 
for graves for those victims whose families wanted them to be 
buried at mecca 
in the islamic faith to die and be buried in mecca is a 
blessing 
saudi officials said the tragedy in the moessem tunnel began 
when a railing on a pedestrian bridge over the tunnel bent sending 
seven pilgrims tumbling to their deaths on top of people coming out 
of the tunnel 
the bodies crashing into the throng touched off panic only 
those at the entrance to the tunnel knew what had happened 
behind them pilgrims continued to move inside the 
1000capacity tunnel filled with an estimated 50000 pushing 
shoving pilgrims 
many died in the frantic stampede others died when the 
ventilation system in the 600yardlong 35footwide tunnel 
stopped inexplicably 
the accident which happened on the first day of the eid aladha 
or feast of sacrifice was described by king fahd as the will of 
god 
hospital sources in jiddah said the victims included arabs 
indonesians malaysians turks pakistanis and indians as well as 
saudis 
it was fate fahd said had they not died there they 
would have died elsewhere and at the same predestined moment 
throughout the world accidents suddenly happen planes crash 
buildings collapse trains collide he said 
he referred to the recent earthquake in iran where at least 
40000 died the earthquake in the moslem state of iran could 
anyone stop that can anyone stop death it is gods will above 
all 
