project launched by the government at the holy sites two years ago 
with these renovation schemes saudi arabia secured moslem world 
backing in 1988 to limit the numbers of pilgrims to 1000 per 
million in each country because of the ongoing work 
the iranians who considered the limit directed against them 
have boycotted the annual pilgrimage season for the three years 
since 
iranian activists or proiranian shiite moslems have spread 
terrorism at the annual hajj since 1986 when security men found 
large quantities of explosives during the pilgrimage 
the following year saudi riot police clashed with pilgrims who 
defied a government ban on political rallies during the religious 
event more than 400 people mostly iranians were killed 
last year one pilgrim was killed and 16 were wounded in two 
bombs explosions sixteen people tried and convicted of the 
attacks were beheaded by the saudi government 
