<TEXT>
major members of nato go to london this week reluctant to change 
the alliance that has prevented conflict during the cold war and 
the advent of nuclear weaponry 
after 41 years of an alliance pitted against the warsaw pact 
the 16 nations that make up the north atlantic treaty organization 
must rethink how they will keep the peace 
the communist governments of eastern europe that supported the 
warsaw pact have been swept away in the last year by popular 
revolutions the new governments for the most part have insisted 
that soviet forces be withdrawn from their soil and that the 
eastwest armed confrontation be ended 
nato leaders on thursday and friday must decide how the western 
world will ensure its safety and what future role the alliance 
might play 
members will wrestle with proposals to change natos focus 
from a military alliance to a political forum its strategy from 
containing communism to regional peacekeeping and even its 
membership with the suggested admission of east germany 
here are some views about the alliances future 
west germany wants nato membership extended to both halves of 
a united germany and to develop the atlantic alliance into a 
stabilityoriented partnership with the soviet union and other 
european countries foreign minister hansdietrich genscher 
has said 
genscher also wants a broader role of the 35nation conference 
on security and cooperation in europe csce which deals with 
military security economic cooperation and human rights 
spanish prime minister felipe gonzalez said last week 
there exists a clear consciousness that the atlantic alliance 
is not replaceable and that the transatlantic link with the 
united states and canada should be maintained 
that someone might propose the elimination of nato would seem 
to me an attempt to ignore the history of the 20th century ignore 
that there was a world war ii he said 
british prime minister margaret thatcher traditionally the 
