<TEXT>
a pamphlet distributed among jewish settlers 
urged them to shoot palestinians and gave detailed instructions on 
how to obtain guns and avoid capture according to media reports 
wednesday 
the anonymous pamphlet quoted by the hebrew daily yediot 
ahronot and state radio advises settlers to gather explosives from 
the army masquerade as soldiers during attacks and leave behind 
misleading evidence 
it says the settlers in the occupied west bank and gaza strip 
should respond to stoning attacks on their cars with gunfire and 
should try to hit and cause much damage 
the pamphlet also urges retribution against palestinians 
you must react to every arab stone with secret revenge acts 
the leaflet was quoted as saying cause damage to arab property 
the reports come at a time of rising tension between settlers 
and palestinians who have carried out an uprising against israeli 
occupation for more than 30 months in the uprising at least 721 
palestinians have been slain by israeli gunfire and 45 israelis 
have died 
the daily haaretz quoted security sources as saying stalled 
peace efforts could push palestinian extremists to attack jewish 
settlements 
liberal politicians have accused the rightwing government of 
encouraging radicals among the settlers 
yediot said the pamphlets were put into settlers mailboxes but 
it was unclear how many were distributed or in which settlements 
the pamphlet was not signed and news reports gave no evidence of 
who printed it 
more than 130 jewish settlements have been built in the west 
bank and gaza since the territories were captured from jordan and 
egypt in the 1967 middle east war about 75000 jews live there 
among 17 million palestinians 
israel harel a settler leader said he checked eight 
settlements and found no sign of the pamphlets this pamphlet is 
simply not known in the settlements he said 
zvi katzover head of the kiryat arba settlement in the west 
bank said the pamphlet was probably done by a fringe group he 
said however the advice should not be ignored to try and 
catch stone throwers at almost any price 
politicians on both left and right expressed fears the pamphlet 
could be evidence that a new jewish underground was forming 
similar to one that targeted and killed several palestinian leaders 
in the early 1980s 
parliament member ran cohen of the liberal citizens rights 
movement said the pamphlet not only calls for the murder of 
innocent arabs but also the impersonation of army soldiers 
cohen said he sent copies of the pamphlet to authorities 
lawmaker geula cohen of the rightwing tehiya party said the 
pamphlet was madness 
this is really an underground not against the arabs but 
against the state of israel she told yediot 
according to the radio the pamphlet outlines a scenario in 
which two settlers are in a car nearing an area where palestinian 
youths often stone settlers cars 
the pamphlet says your friend moves into the back seat 
handgun in hand in front of you a stone is thrown your friend 
opens a window and empties his magazine he tries to hit and cause 
much damage 
the pamphlet goes on to to say that to mislead investigators 
the settlers should then sprinkle on the roadside empty cartridges 
not from their own weapons 
among the instructions quoted from the pamphlet were 
collect explosives fuses delaying fuses detonators the 
primary source the army 
arm yourself with an m16 assault rifle take the weapon 
from your settlements armory or from your army unit 
when you go on an operation wear army fatigues and a 
stocking cap 
how not to be caught if you use your weapon do not report 
to a civilian control center or the military wipe fingerprints 
from the weapon 
