temporarily suspended plans to kill 30000 seals in response to 
mounting criticism from local and foreign animal rights groups 
environment minister gert kotze acknowledged that public outrage 
was behind his decision to reconsider plans to kill 25000 cape fur 
seal cubs and 5000 adult male seals on the northwest coast later 
