<TEXT>
two dozen wealthy nations on wednesday 
extended their aid program for poland and hungary to four other 
east european nations that shed their communist ways and switched 
to market economies 
agreement to grant financial and other aid to bulgaria 
czechoslovakia yugoslavia and east germany came at a meeting of 
foreign ministers of 24 nations including those of the european 
community the united states japan canada and australia 
romania was excluded because of doubts about its commitment to 
democratic reforms 
aid to the soviet union was discussed but no decision was taken 
west germany wants quick action on such aid the united states and 
japan among others do not 
