reforms in the soviet union 
we take note of the fact that the soviet union is spending 
somewhere between 18 and 25 percent of its gross domestic product 
on military expenditures he told reporters 
baker said the united states has problems the soviet expenditure 
of between 9 billion and 15 billion a year to support regimes 
around the world that in the past at least have been hostile to the 
views and interests and principles of the united states 
the soviet union unlike the four countries added to the western 
aid program wednesday has not asked for western aid 
the 24 nations also disagreed over creating a special fund of 
possibly 10 billion to 12 billion as a financial safety net for 
east european nations 
frans andriessen the meeting chairman and ec external relations 
commissioner advanced the plan but the ministers said this was 
mostly a question for existing institutions such as the world bank 
and the international monetary fund 
wednesdays meeting fixed no specific aid figures 
these will emerge as each donor makes pledges in food money 
credits loan guarantees and other assistance 
it was a conference designed to take stock see whether we 
should and could decided to add countries to the aid package 
