days after a unmediated ceasefire halted the eightyear persian 
gulf war 
although velayati and aziz were present in the four rounds of 
peace talks held since 1988 the two men did not speak directly to 
each other instead relaying their comments through perez de 
cuellar 
the earlier negotiations stalled almost immediately over the 
question of priorities iran insisted on an iraqi withdrawal from 
territories occupied in the last weeks of the war 
iraq insisted that iran agree first to the dredging of the 
shattalarab waterway of war debris the waterway marks the 
southern border of the two nations 
the common border ran down the middle of the channel before the 
war but iraq has demanded full sovereignty over the shattalarab 
its main outlet to the gulf 
before leaving geneva wednesday velayati told reporters he was 
optimstic that the talks would move ahead 
during the meeting we found out that iraq and iran both of 
them now are more flexible than in the past he said without 
elaborating 
perez de cuellar who in previous talks relayed statements 
between the two ministers said tuesdays meeting was a 
psychological breakthrough though nothing substantive was 
discussed 
