mayor art agnos has ordered police to break 
up a sprawling encampment of homeless people just outside city 
hall substituting a resettlement program critics call insufficient 
agnos order which takes effect friday directs police to begin 
enforcing laws against sleeping in public places 
the mayor an unabashed liberal democrat tolerated the 
encampment of as many as 350 people for two years because he said 
there was no workable alternative 
this week the city took over operation of two shelters intended 
to provide comprehensive services such as alcohol detoxification 
and job counseling to the homeless city officials say the plan is 
a new approach of offering a port of reentry to society 
advocates for the homeless charge that the two service shelters 
are insufficient and understaffed and wont solve the citys 
housing problem they say the agnos program will reshuffle the 
homeless by forcing out 215 people staying in a private shelter 
taken over by the city 
they said the new policy will break up couples and force many 
people into jails doorways or alleys 
whats going to happen friday night is san francisco will 
start criminalizing homelessness said josh brandon of the 
coalition on homelessness 
the city tells you there are 329 beds in our new system 
what they neglect to tell you is 215 are already full brandon 
said 
only men will receive beds in the new multiservice shelters 
during the first few weeks of the program women will continue to 
be placed in existing housing programs until beds are added to the 
new shelters by mid to late summer 
some women say they shun the existing programs because they 
involve placement in seedy unsafe hotels or have too many 
restrictions 
cristina jaskula who has been living outside city hall since 
february says she and her husband would rather remain free 
than be separated in order to have shelter 
a shelter is like being in prison said jaskula 42 
theres no freedom of movement 
in the past two years the number of homeless people in the 
treeshaded civic center park has grown into the hundreds it has 
been dubbed camp agnos by some of its residents and critics 
including city employees who used to have lunch in the park but 
have been driven away by the shabbiness and human waste 
