designed for maximum speed and memoryprocessing capacity 
the top of the line the model 60 is capable of speeds of up to 
500 million instructions per second and can store up to 128 
trillion bits of data the equivalent of about 200000 years of a 
typical englishlanguage newspaper nec said 
last month japans hitachi ltd announced its m880 series of 
mainframe computers with a maximum speed of 155 million 
instructions per second which it said was then the fastest in the 
world ibms top model has a speed of 122 million instructions per 
second it said 
the hitachi computers are compatible with ibm machines while 
necs mainframes are not making direct comparisons difficult 
but the new nec computers appeared to put the company 
significantly ahead of its rivals in the competition for top speed 
ibm the worlds largest maker of computers is reportedly 
developing a new mainframe computer expected to debut next year 
generalpurpose mainframe computers are intended for varied 
office and business use while supercomputers are designed 
specifically for scientific calculations and therefore can operate 
more rapidly 
necs executive vice president yukio mizuno said the system 
3800 computers are designed to handle large data bases for one or 
more companies 
up until now large mainframes generally served a single 
company but increasingly they are being used to create networks 
between several companies such as a manufacturer and its 
wholesalers he said 
seven versions of the computers are available ranging from one 
to six processors the company said a processor is the brain 
of a computer and several processors give a machine an ability to 
process information more rapidly 
monthly lease fees range from 330000 to 19 million nec 
said it said it plans to sell about 200 systems over the next five 
years 
