a bomb damaged the offices of 
an antiapartheid newspaper wednesday a day after rightwing 
extremists claimed responsibility for recent attacks against whites 
wanting to end segregation 
the predawn explosion at the empty offices of the 
afrikaanslanguage newspaper vrye weekblad was the fifth attack in 
as many nights against whites opposed to apartheid 
the bomb caused only minor damage no one has been hurt in any 
of the explosions all in johannesburg 
a man claiming to belong to a rightwing extremist group the 
white wolves said his organization was responsible for the recent 
blasts he made the claim in a phone call tuesday to the citizen a 
progovernment newspaper 
the editor of vrye weekblad max du preez said an unidentified 
caller phoned him at home wednesday morning and warned that the 
attack was only a beginning 
the attacks on the four preceding nights were at the office and 
the home of one antiapartheid city council member at the home of 
