<TEXT>
american telephone and telegraph co 
has agreed to buy selected parts of western union corps business 
services unit for 180 million 
western union of upper saddle river has been having financial 
troubles for the past few years and is in the midst of a 
restructuring 
under the agreement announced tuesday atampt would buy the assets 
used to provide western unions easylink electronic mail service 
and its telex and packetswitched services 
atampt would take on western unions 1160 business services 
employees and the units customer base said john smart president 
of business communications services in a news release from atampts 
basking ridge offices 
the agreement does not include western union priority services 
which provides mailgram priority letter and custom letter 
services it leaves the company with approximately 2500 employees 
said western union spokesman warren bechtel 
the transaction completes the transformation of western union 
from a telecommunications company to a financial services and 
paperbased messaging business said robert j amman president and 
chief executive officer of western union 
the deal would also help the company pay a major portion of its 
new first priority notes issued to bondholders as part of the 
companys restructuring said amman on june 14 the securities and 
exchange commission approved western unions plan to swap 530 
million in debt for new notes and stock 
western union wrote off 603 million in special charges in the 
first quarter of 1988 in connection with the planned sale of the 
companys microwave voiceswitching facilities in 1988 the 
company reported 32 million in losses 
faced with making a 51 million biannual interest payment by 
june 15 the company told regulators in march that it would have to 
seek bankruptcy court protection if it couldnt meet its debt 
interest payments 
atampt spokeswoman lynn newman said the western union unit earned 
more than 629 million last year and atampt is looking forward to its 
continued profitability 
it wasnt a huge amount of money for a buy but were getting 
a good match with our existing electronic messaging system and 
weve got the added customer base said newman 
the sale needs regulatory approval and is conditioned on 
completion of a western union debt restructuring plan the 
companies said the deal should be completed by september 
